  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Community-led urban slum upgrading programme (CUSUP)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Over 70% of urban dwellers in Lusaka live in slums which are characterised by overcrowding, lack of adequate water and sanitation, insecure tenure and poor quality housing. Government policies, practices and resources have failed to adequately address these challenges and most city development plans exclude comprehensive information about slums and informal settlements. This project will develop the information base needed for informal settlements to be recognised as an important part of Lusaka and establish a means for the rights of urban poor communities to be included in the planning and provision of public services. The expected results will include better data and knowledge about Lusaka&apos;s informal settlements, a comprehensive citywide slum prevention strategy and enhanced capacity of local authorities and communities around slum upgrading.</narrative>
  </description>
